chug
Homonym Number:
Word Class:verb
Sense Number:
Definition:down (an alcoholic or other drink), especially quickly or without pausing.
Origin:[none]
Register: informal

Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:chug-a-lug
Pronunciation:
Notes: (also as noun the downing of a drink quickly or without pausing; a drinking bout.)
Citations
