Source: Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author: McGILL
Vol / Page: 28
Edition:
Quote: <i>chug</i> to drink alcohol;<i> chugalug</i> act of drinking, usually a beer, in one gulp, or a drinking bout; eg `Fancy a few chugs after work, Nobby?' ANZ.
